<Window x:Class="FileSizeAnalyzerGUI.HelpWindow"
        xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
        xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
        Title="Help" Height="450" Width="600"
        WindowStartupLocation="CenterOwner" ShowInTaskbar="False">
    <ScrollViewer Margin="15">
        <StackPanel>
            <TextBlock Text="FileSizeAnalyzer Pro Help" FontSize="18" FontWeight="Bold" Margin="0,0,0,10"/>

            <TextBlock FontWeight="Bold" Margin="0,10,0,5">Scanning</TextBlock>
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap">
                1. Select a drive from the dropdown or click 'Browse' to choose a specific folder. You can also type a path directly into the text box.
                <LineBreak/>
                2. Click the 'Scan' button to begin the analysis. The scan can be stopped at any time with the 'Stop Scan' button.
            </TextBlock>

            <TextBlock FontWeight="Bold" Margin="0,10,0,5">Filtering</TextBlock>
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap">
                - Use the dropdown menus to filter results by file size or date modified.
                <LineBreak/>
                - In the text box, you can filter by multiple file extensions. Separate them with a comma or semicolon (e.g., .jpg, .log; .tmp).
                <LineBreak/>
                - Click 'Apply Filters' to update the 'File List' tab with your filter criteria.
            </TextBlock>

            <TextBlock FontWeight="Bold" Margin="0,10,0,5">Interacting with Results</TextBlock>
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap">
                - Right-click on any file or folder in the lists to open its location or move it to the Recycle Bin.
                <LineBreak/>
                - Double-clicking an item in the 'File List' or 'Duplicates' tab will also prompt to move it to the Recycle Bin.
            </TextBlock>

            <TextBlock FontWeight="Bold" Margin="0,10,0,5">Tabs</TextBlock>
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap">
                - <Bold>Directory Tree:</Bold> A hierarchical view of your scanned folder, sorted by size.
                <LineBreak/>
                - <Bold>File List:</Bold> A list of all files found, which can be filtered using the controls at the top.
                <LineBreak/>
                - <Bold>Largest Files:</Bold> A quick view of the top 100 largest files from the scan.
                <LineBreak/>
                - <Bold>Empty Folders:</Bold> A list of all folders that contain no files or subfolders.
                <LineBreak/>
                - <Bold>Duplicates:</Bold> A grouped view of files that have identical content.
                <LineBreak/>
                - <Bold>Treemap:</Bold> A visual representation of the currently selected folder in the 'Directory Tree' tab. Click a rectangle to navigate to that item in the tree.
            </TextBlock>
        </StackPanel>
    </ScrollViewer>
</Window>
